+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Classified every visible thread from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before editing code, then applied only the changes needed for the three actionable threads.
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The authoritative triage record is in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- `build_policy_preview` now normalizes `approval_state` before calling `build_preview_payload`.
+- Result: `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)` now passes `human_review_required` into the preview builder instead of the retired alias.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- Fallback payloads now include:
+  - `approval_state`
+  - `requires_human_review`
+- Result: unavailable-preview responses preserve the same approval semantics as live preview responses.
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Extended the fallback test to assert `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
+- Added a regression test covering `manual_review` normalization through `build_policy_preview` when `preview_enabled=False`.
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback payload example to show:
+  - `"approval_state": "human_review_required"`
+  - `"requires_human_review": true`
+- Updated the note so it describes the corrected behavior instead of the stale reviewer write-up.
+
+## Validation
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Results:
+
+- `tests.test_preview`: passed (`Ran 3 tests ... OK`)
+- `tests.test_approval_router`: passed (`Ran 2 tests ... OK`)
+
+## Constraints Honored
+
+- No changes were made under `.github/review_export/`.
+- `tests/test_approval_router.py` was left untouched.
+- `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md` was not modified.
+- No `legacy_preview_hint` behavior was introduced.
+- No network access was used.
