+## PR-214 Thread Replies
+
+### T-214-01
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py`. The fallback payload now preserves both `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled=False`, so the unavailable-preview response stays aligned with the live payload shape.
+
+### T-214-02
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. This reports the same reopened fallback preview regression, so the fix is covered by the `src/policy/preview.py` payload update and the new fallback regression test.
+
+### T-214-03
+Marked obsolete. The suggestion points at an outdated hunk and asks to revive legacy preview behavior; I did not apply it on the current branch and did not add any `legacy_preview_hint` path.
+
+### T-214-04
+Added regression coverage in `tests/test_preview.py` for `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`. The new test asserts fallback status plus normalized `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+### T-214-05
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example now shows `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`, matching the corrected payload.
